<% provide(:title, 'FAQ') %>
<h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

<h3>Is this a free service?</h3>
<li><h5>Yes and no </h5></li>
<li><h5>Yes in that if you use the bike share there will be no charges</h5></li>
<li><h5>No in if you do not return the bike, cause major damage to the bike, etc we will have to charge you</h5></li>

<h3>Who can join this program?</h3>
<li><h5>Any RIT Student, Faculty, or Staff can borrow a bike!</h5></li>
<li><h5>We are in the process of allowing friends and family to borrow a bike.</h5></li>


<h3>Are there any fees associated with renting a program?</h3>
<h5>The Rental Service is free, however there are possible charges for misuse of bikes or the service,
  as outlined in the rental agreement</h5>
<h6>
  <ul>
    <li>Late return is: $5 per 24 hours that it is late</li>
    <li>Failure to return bike after 4 weeks is: The cost of replacing the bike</li>
    <li>Lost Key is: $30, to replace the U-Lock </li>
    <li>Damaged Key is: $5, too replace the key</li>
    <li>Lost Bike is:  The cost of replacing the bike</li>
    <li>Bike Damage to the point of needing to buy a replacement is: The cost of replacing the bike</li>
  </ul>
</h6>

<h3>Do I need to wear a helmet?</h3>
<li><h5>Wearing a helmet is suggested, we are not providing any users of this program with helmets</h5></li>

<h3>Where do I check a bike?</h3>
<li><h5>This program is currently being run through the Residential Office in the Kate-Gleason Dorm</h5></li>

<h3>Is there anything that I need to do before borrowing a bike?</h3>
<li><h5>Yes! The one thing that you must do first is to register on this website.</h5></li>
<li><h5>To register for this program, click the login button in the top right.</h5></li>
<li><h5>After logging in click the register button in the top right.</h5></li>
<li><h5>Read and check off that you have read the waiver.</h5></li>
<li><h5>Fill in the necessary information on the register page</h5></li>
<li><h5>Click Update User and you are Finished!</h5></li>